[2m[2mSession[0m: [1;33mdeepseek_deepseek-v4-flash-integration-bug-trial-1[0m[0m
## Summary

**Status: `EXCELLENT`** — all 6 trials pass, lock detected, score 1.0.

### What was wrong (3 bugs)

| Bug | Root cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| **Overselling** (negative stock) | TOCTOU race in `decrement()`: `await asyncio.sleep()` between `if self._stock >= quantity` and `self._stock -= quantity` — concurrent coroutines both pass the check before either mutates | `asyncio.Lock` wraps `check_stock`, `decrement`, and `increment` so the check-and-mutate is atomic |
| **Ghost charges** (charged, no item) | Flow order: `check_stock → charge → decrement`. When `decrement` fails (due to race above), customer is charged but gets nothing | Reserve-before-charge: `decrement → charge → (on failure) increment`. No charge unless stock is already reserved |
| **Duplicate charges** (same order_id charged twice) | `PaymentGateway.charge` has no idempotency check | Skip charge if `order_id` already exists in `self.charges` |

### Changed files

- `checkout.py` — inverted flow to decrement-first; release stock on payment failure
- `inventory.py` — added `asyncio.Lock` to all stock methods for atomic check-and-mutate
- `payments.py` — added idempotency check by `order_id` before appending charge
